        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 15 at 2:37PM CDT by NWS Aberdeen SD</headline>
        <description>At 236 PM CDT, trained weather spotters reported a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from near Putney to Cresbard.
Movement was east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Trained weather spotters.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Aberdeen, Warner, Mina Lake Rec Area, Bath, Columbia, Claremont,
Putney, Cresbard, Mansfield, Chelsea, Mina, Houghton, Tacoma Park,
South Scatterwood Lake, Sand Lake Wildlife Refuge, North Scatterwood
Lake, and Richmond Lake Rec Area.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
